  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH992427.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H C F Cs\"><math alttext=\"H C F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>HCFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> were originally introduced as a solution to help phase out the use of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C F Cs\"><math alttext=\"C F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>CFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following most likely contributed to the increased levels of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H C F Cs\"><math alttext=\"H C F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>HCFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in the stratosphere over the past 30 years?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Thermal inversions in the troposphere</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
